Dialogue: 0,00:00:00.000,00:00:06.160,辉英,,0,0,0,,If u0 is equal to u, it's still going to be u, exactly.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:06.680,00:00:12.820,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is because we just wrote the equation without the superscripts, right?
Dialogue: 0,00:00:12.900,00:00:19.080,辉英,,0,0,0,,Without the superscript, the equation is exactly satisfied by the solution to the linear equations.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:20.480,00:00:27.420,辉英,,0,0,0,,So if u0 is already u, then the left-hand side is u1.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:27.420,00:00:31.580,辉英,,0,0,0,,And u1 has to be also u in order for this equation to be satisfied.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:32.720,00:00:38.240,辉英,,0,0,0,,Well, unless d is degenerate, unless d has zero entries, it's a diagonal matrix, right?
Dialogue: 0,00:00:38.300,00:00:43.920,辉英,,0,0,0,,So if all the diagonal parts are non-zero, then u1 can only be u.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:45.440,00:00:48.820,辉英,,0,0,0,,And therefore, if u1 is equal to u, u2 also has to be u.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:48.960,00:00:51.660,辉英,,0,0,0,,If u2 has to be u, u3 also has to be u, etc.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:51.660,00:00:56.580,辉英,,0,0,0,,So if you start it with the right solution, you'll always end up with the right solution.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:57.680,00:00:59.520,辉英,,0,0,0,,Of course, that's a big assumption, right?
Dialogue: 0,00:00:59.660,00:01:02.260,辉英,,0,0,0,,So you almost never start with the right solution.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:03.000,00:01:04.120,辉英,,0,0,0,,So what do you get?
Dialogue: 0,00:01:04.720,00:01:07.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,What do you get if you don't have the right solution to start with?
Dialogue: 0,00:01:08.220,00:01:09.460,辉英,,0,0,0,,So let's define.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:10.080,00:01:12.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,Let's look at now the error equation.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:13.380,00:01:15.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,So the error equation is looking at,
Dialogue: 0,00:01:15.280,00:01:26.220,辉英,,0,0,0,,so if I define solution error ek to be the difference between the solution I have minus the real solution,
Dialogue: 0,00:01:27.420,00:01:35.380,辉英,,0,0,0,,well, in practice, I never know what ek is because I don't know the true solution.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:36.660,00:01:42.060,辉英,,0,0,0,,But if I can derive a governing equation for the evolution of ek,
Dialogue: 0,00:01:42.880,00:01:48.880,辉英,,0,0,0,,we can analyze is the solution error becoming smaller and smaller or becoming larger and larger as I iterate.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:48.880,00:01:56.880,辉英,,0,0,0,,And we want to construct the method or derive conditions for the method so that ek is going to,
Dialogue: 0,00:01:56.880,00:01:57.020,辉英,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,00:01:57.020,00:01:57.080,辉英,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,00:01:57.080,00:01:57.140,辉英,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,00:01:57.140,00:01:57.400,辉英,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,00:01:57.400,00:01:57.420,辉英,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,00:01:57.420,00:01:59.480,辉英,,0,0,0,,decreasing as I increase k.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:00.400,00:02:03.440,辉英,,0,0,0,,So how do we derive the equation for ek?
Dialogue: 0,00:02:04.160,00:02:08.700,辉英,,0,0,0,,We subtract this equation with the superscript.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:10.080,00:02:16.820,辉英,,0,0,0,,We subtract the equation without a superscript from the equation with the superscript.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:18.160,00:02:24.100,辉英,,0,0,0,,By doing this, the left-hand side would be du k plus 1 minus du.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:24.880,00:02:27.400,辉英,,0,0,0,,The right-hand side would be b,
Dialogue: 0,00:02:27.400,00:02:28.520,辉英,,0,0,0,,minus l,
Dialogue: 0,00:02:28.520,00:02:28.960,辉英,,0,0,0,,u,
Dialogue: 0,00:02:28.960,00:02:29.580,辉英,,0,0,0,,k,
Dialogue: 0,00:02:29.580,00:02:30.620,辉英,,0,0,0,,minus u,
Dialogue: 0,00:02:30.620,00:02:31.020,辉英,,0,0,0,,u,
