Dialogue: 0,00:02:58.180,00:02:58.780,辉英,,0,0,0,,cancels.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:58.780,00:03:05.480,辉英,,0,0,0,,What we are left with is l plus u,
Dialogue: 0,00:03:05.480,00:03:08.100,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I think we have a minus sign here,
Dialogue: 0,00:03:08.100,00:03:09.380,辉英,,0,0,0,,times ek.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:09.380,00:03:16.580,辉英,,0,0,0,,So the last thing we want to do is further simplify this by multiplying a d inverse.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:16.580,00:03:22.780,辉英,,0,0,0,,Remember, the method only works if d has non-zero diagonals.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:22.780,00:03:26.500,辉英,,0,0,0,,So let's multiply a d inverse on both equations,
Dialogue: 0,00:03:26.500,00:03:26.980,辉英,,0,0,0,,both equations.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:26.980,00:03:31.480,辉英,,0,0,0,,So the left-hand side becomes ek plus 1,
Dialogue: 0,00:03:31.480,00:03:37.780,辉英,,0,0,0,,the right-hand side becomes minus d inverse times l plus u times ek.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:37.780,00:03:40.420,辉英,,0,0,0,,Good here?
Dialogue: 0,00:03:40.420,00:03:47.580,辉英,,0,0,0,,So we can start analyzing whether the ek would increase or decrease over time.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:47.580,00:03:53.660,辉英,,0,0,0,,What determines if ek is going to increase or decrease over time?
Dialogue: 0,00:03:53.660,00:03:54.780,辉英,,0,0,0,,The eigenvalue.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:54.780,00:03:55.780,辉英,,0,0,0,,Yes, the eigenvalue.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:55.780,00:03:56.180,辉英,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:56.180,00:03:56.780,辉英,,0,0,0,,So the eigenvalue is going to be the eigenvalue of the equation.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:56.780,00:03:58.680,辉英,,0,0,0,,The eigenvalue of this matrix.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:58.680,00:04:01.940,辉英,,0,0,0,,This matrix is so important it has a name.
